Note: the following is a test for scopes.
Create a function TestScope with argument test.
Upon calling TestScope do:
Set the value of test to 0.
That's it.

Create a variable test.
Create another variable called arg.
Set the value of test to one.
Set the value of arg to five.
TestScope arg.
TestScope arg.
If test equals zero or arg differs from zero do:
Display "Test failed!" and a newline.
Stop because of the failure.
That's it.
Display "Test passed!" and a newline.
